resources.string:
A database table can store different data. And in that table each column can have a field assigned to a different Data Type.
\nFor example we can have a column to store DATA. Another column to record just NUMBERS. Or TEXT.
\nIf we try to insert text into a column that only allows numbers, the database will throw an error.
\nSome of the Data types are:
\n
\nINT - Integer from -2.147.483.648 to 2.147.483.647;
\nSMALLINT - Integer from -32768 to 32767;
\nMONEY - Monetary or currency values of -922.337.203.685.477,5808 to 922.337.203.685.477,5807;
\nDATE - Date;
\nDATETIME - Date and time;
\nCHAR - Character data types that are of fixed length;
\nVARCHAR - Character data types that are variable length;
\nTEXT - Fixed and variable-length data types for storing large Unicode and non-Unicode character and binary data.
\n
\nAmong others, such as:
\nDECIMAL;
\nNUMERIC;
\nFLOAT;
\nREAL.

Following the example query, the guideline is to create a Table with the name CUSTOMER. And that has the Columns:
        \nCODE of type INT;
        \nNAME of type CHAR;
        \nCPF of type CHAR.
